https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Why do the New Mutants exist? Why are they a team? Cyclops runs the X-Men as one giant army, not separate squads. So, how can he justify the solo nature of the New Mutants?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: New Mutants (2009) #2
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: RETURN OF LEGION PART 2 Last time Legion reared his head, he created the Age of Apocalpyse.  Do Cannonball, Karma, Magma, Moonstar and Magik have much hope of stopping him now?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: New Mutants (2009) #3
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: RETURN OF LEGION PART 3 Each personality in Legion's head has a super power and it seems like there's a new one every day. Dani Moonstar is at the center of this, but what can a depowered mutant do against a foe that has a million ways to kill her?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: New Mutants (2009) #4
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: RETURN OF LEGION PART 4 Can Cannonball, Sunspot, Magma and Dani Moonstar defeat a villain with dozens of super-powered multiple personalities? Plus, Karma and Magik are stuck inside Legion's mind.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: New Mutants (2009) #5
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Warlock is back! Everyone's favorite alien is back on Earth, but why? Plus, witness the vicious battle between Cannonball and Dani Moonstar!

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: New Mutants (2009) #7
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: NECROSHA: NEW MUTANTS, CHAPTER 2 Doug Ramsey isn't the only one back from the grave as the New Mutants' old enemies the Hellions come calling. Old grudges (and enemies, for that matter) don't die easy.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: New Mutants (2009) #8
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: NECROSHA: NEW MUTANTS, CHAPTER 3 The New Mutants' part in NECROSHA comes to a close here! It's Doug Ramsey and the Hellions vs. Sam and his crew and it ain't looking good for our friends in the yellow and black.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: New Mutants (2009) #9
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: What is Illyana Rasputin up to? She recently returned from who knows where with knowledge that she says is from the future. https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Punisher Noir (2009) #1
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: It's the Roaring Twenties and mobster Dutch Schultz's iron-fisted reign is about to meet its greatest challenge. But will the greatest threat to his criminal empire come from Thomas Dewey and the government? Will it come from fellow mobsters like Lucky Luciano or Al Capone? No, it'll come in the form of a man sporting a familiar skull symbol and a gun in his hand. Because once the Punisher hits the scene, the mean streets are about to get a whole lot meaner.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Punisher Noir (2009) #2
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: Frank Castle has come face to face with the evil that men do, in the trench warfare of the muddy battlefields of World War I. He's come home only to see his city carved up amongst the mob families, as the power of organized crime syndicates rise up to challenge that of the government. In reaction to the Punisher's War on Crime, two hitmen are dispatched to deal with him permanently: a killer whose face is a roadmap of hell, and the biggest, meanest mountain of muscle ever to come from the streets of Harlem. With Jigsaw and Barracuda on the scene, "paint the town red" will take on a whole new meaning.

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Punisher Noir (2009) #3
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: "TWO DOWN..." The Punisher has cut a bloody swath through the organized crime families of prohibition-era New York City and now they're starting to fight back. Does Frank have what it takes to take down Jigsaw and Barracuda? The real question is, will there be anything left of him, if he does?

https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.title: Punisher Noir (2009) #4
https://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/sto.description: The Punisher has torn through the New York underworld and now there's only one man standing between him and the man he's been aching to kill for years. But this man's got a major bone to pick with Frank. It all comes to a head in one violent night at the Bronx Zoo. The Punisher is about to experience what it's like to be on the receiving end of some payback...from Russia with love.
